  <title translate="true">RmaMF6: Activate PEST</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RmaMF6: Activate PEST</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To activate PEST, select </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Model|PEST Properties...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and check the checkbox labeled </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Use PEST</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> on the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Basic</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane as illustrated below. Be sure that the PEST directory is set to the directory where PEST is installed. By default, the PEST mode is set to “regularization” on the “Control Data|Mode and Dimensions” pane. The regularization mode activates Tikhonov regularization.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="RmaMf6ActivatePest.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><title translate="true">Screen capture of the PEST Properties dialog box illustrating activating PEST.</title><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Screen capture of the PEST Properties dialog box illustrating activating PEST.]]></caption></image></para>
  </body>
